cp

this is actually for coping a file with different name.

  calvin@localhost:~/Documents/secret$ cp mySecretNote.txt copyFile.txt

  Noot : after cp we need to write our valid file then a space then write the new file name!

We can also copy a file to another place 
calvin@localhost:~/Documents/secret$ cp -R file1.txt /tmp/
so this will copy the same txt file in tmp
